        "title": "fix(codex): release post-tool raw assistant turns",
        "body": "## Status\nParked after review. This PR should not merge as-is.\n\nIt changes post-tool raw assistant progress from the documented terminal-guard path into assistant-output release. That can deliver a progress/status line as the final user-visible answer without receiving `turn/completed`.\n\nRelated semantic decision: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/84137\n\n## Original proposal\n- Treat post-tool raw assistant message completions as releasable assistant output instead of a completion-idle failure.\n- Preserve the configurable post-tool raw assistant idle window for that release path.\n- Disarm the competing completion watchdog so the release window can win, then interrupt the stuck app-server turn best-effort.\n- Update the targeted turn-watch expectations for post-tool and post-native-tool raw assistant stalls.\n\n## Due diligence\n- ClawSweeper's P1 finding is valid: this turns possible progress text into final output.\n- Current docs say post-tool raw assistant progress keeps waiting for `turn/completed` while a completion-idle guard stays armed.\n- Issue #84137 explicitly leaves the default post-tool semantics open for maintainer decision.\n- The observed real text, `The data model needs to change...`, is progress, not a final answer.\n\n## Tests\n- Not run, per request.",
